Orange Democratic Movement is currently holding the party's National Governing Convention (NGC) meeting at Bomas of Kenya. Presided over by the party leader Raila Odinga, the meeting is expected to ratify the party's nomination rules. The top organ is also expected to stamp NEC's decision to have the election of national officials rescheduled to next year. ODM on Saturday will hold its National Delegates Convention (NDC) at Kasarani gymnasium. This is where Azimio la Umoja coalition party - Raila's vehicle in the August polls - will be unveiled.